</tr><tr><td style="text-align: left;"><strong>Additional Services</strong>
<p>				If a worker has failed Steps 1 and 2, AND meets the DSM-V criteria for opioid use disorder, the department or insurer may cover up to 6 months of addiction treatment through a licensed chemical dependency treatment center as an aid to recovery. A list of treatment centers certified by the Division of Behavior Health and Recovery is available at <a href="http://www.dshs.wa.gov/dbhr/dadirectory.shtml">http://www.dshs.wa.gov/dbhr/dadirectory.shtml</a> External Web site Policy.</p>
<p>				Refer to the original guideline document for more information about additional services.</p>
