<td style="text-align: left; background-color: rgb(204, 204, 204);"><strong>TREATMENT FOR OPIOID DEPENDENCE</strong></td>
</tr><tr><td style="text-align: left;"><strong>Substance Use Disorders</strong>
<p>				Individuals with alcohol and other SUDs are at increased risk for poor retention in care, poor adherence, and virologic failure. Several adherence strategies not recommended for general clinic populations are effective among those with SUDs.</p>
<p>				Recommendation 27: Offering buprenorphine or methadone to opioid-dependent patients is recommended (<strong>II A</strong>).</p>
<p>				Recommendation 29: Integration of DAART into MMT for opioid-dependent patients is recommended (<strong>II B</strong>).</p></td>
</tr><tr><td colspan="7" scope="row" style="text-align: left;">
